Source:
  - Title: Treasury of Traditional Wisdom
    Page: 126
  - Title: Mânava-dharma-sâstra
    Location: II 162
Tags:
  - Sacrifice-Death=Sacrifice and Suffering=Contemptus Mundi
  - Sacrifice-Death=Renunciation-Detachment=Indifference to Pleasure and Pain
---
A Brahman should ever shrink from honour as from poison, and should always be
desirous of disrespect as if of ambrosia.
